New Transport Minister Joe Maswanganyi says he has not signed any documents since being sworn in and he will be meeting with former minister Dipuo Peters soon. PRETORIA - New Transport Minister Joe Maswanganyi says he s ready, willing and able to take over the department and make a difference in the lives of South Africans. Maswanganyi takes over from Dipuo Peters, who was also given the boot last Thursday. Minister Maswanganyi comes into the transport ministry having already played a role in Parliament's portfolio committee on transport. He started his address on Monday by thanking all his predecessors, including Peters. I want to take this opportunity to thank the ministers of transport - since 1994 and recently Minister Peters. He says he will continue to build South Africa. In this 23rd year of our freedom, our mission is the quest for a united, democratic, non-sexist, non-racial and prosperous South Africa. The new minister says he has not signed any documents since being sworn in and will be meeting with Peters soon for a formal handover. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)